-----------------
ETEQ Microsystems 
-----------------

--- NOTICE!  COUGAR M/Boards that have one ETEQ chip marked "B" while
             the other is either marked "A" or has no revision letter
             require Rev A bios.  Use Rev B bios only if both ETEQ
             chips are marked "B" or later.

Filename   Port      Description
--------   -------   ---------------------------------------------------------
V018B301   ETEQ301   386, 82C491/2  "COUGAR", Rev A    **ONLY**
V018B303   ETEQ303   386, 82C491/2  "COUGAR", Rev B,C  **NOT Rev A**
V018B304   ETEQ304   x018B303  (TL-)
V018B305   ETEQ305   x018B303  (TL+)

V018B311   ETEQ311   386, 82C491/3  "BOBCAT", Rev A    (non-cache)
V018B314   ETEQ314   x018B311  (TL-)
V018B315   ETEQ315   x018B311  (TL+)

V018B401   ETEQ401   486, 82C491/2  "COUGAR", Rev A    **ONLY**  
V018B403   ETEQ403   486, 82C491/2  "COUGAR", Rev B,C  **NOT Rev A**  
V018B404   ETEQ404   x018B403  (CL-)
V018B405   ETEQ405   x018B403  (CL+)

V046B321   ETEQ321   386, 82C4901/2  "BENGAL" (WriteBack)
V046B324   ETEQ324   x046B321  (TL-)
V046B325   ETEQ325   x046B321  (TL+)

V046B420   ETEQ421   486, 82C4901/2  "BENGAL" (WriteBack)
V046B428   ETEQ428   x046B420  (CL-)
V046B429   ETEQ429   x046B420  (CL+)

V073B330   ETEQ330   386sx, IBM-SLC  "PANDA"


-----------------------------------------------------------------
 8042 Turbo/Turbo-LED control:  (T-) (T+) (TL-) (TL+) (CL-) (CL+)
-----------------------------------------------------------------

Hot-Key TURBO and/or LED control via keystrokes  <CTRL> <ALT> <-/+>  will
simultaneously activate all commonly used 8042 pins: 23,24, 27,28,29,30.

The system board layout must connect one of these pins to an existing
Turbo/LED circuit.  Consideration should be given to the remaining pins
which are also driven.  MR BIOS (r) 8042 or AMI KF keyboard controller
may be used for this purpose.  Award, Phoenix, and Quadtel 8042's cannot
be used with any MR BIOS (r) version designated as having this special
8042 functionality.

                  Active
Legend  Function  State   Description
------  --------  -----   -------------------------------------------- 
(T-)    Turbo      Low    8042 turbo/LED circuit ONLY (no chipset register
(T+)    Turbo      High   turbo).  Also, Setup Utility SPEED screen appears.

(TL-)   Turbo-LED  Low    Both chipset turbo and 8042 pins are activated.
(TL+)   Turbo-LED  High

(CL-)   Cache-LED  Low    Used mainly with 486, Cache state indicates "turbo".
(CL+)   Cache-LED  High

